What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Shale Gas Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Shale Gas Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the shale gas market will witness a CAGR of 8.26% for the forecast period of 2021-2028 and is likely to reach at USD 139.51 billion by 2028.

Shale gas is natural gas that can be created from shale rock and deposits underground. It is the largest source of natural gas in the United States and is expected to be a potential energy source for the rest of the world. Shale gas is believed to have reduced greenhouse gas emissions to the environment.

Reduction in the prices of natural gas and environmental protection and growing awareness about the benefits of natural gas are the major drivers influencing the growth of the shale gas market. Furthermore, easy availability of abundant source of shale gas and high growth in the supply and distribution infrastructure will accelerate the shale gas market growth rate.

Also, technological advancement and innovations associated with shale gas extraction will provide beneficial opportunities for the shale gas market growth.

However, high amount of capital invested for the project of shale gas and extraction of chemicals and waste into water bodies will hamper the growth of the shale gas market. Harmful effects of horizontal drilling on the environment will challenge the shale gas market growth rate.

